<paragraph id="0D382D36FFCDFFD1FF3CFA494EB962FF" blockId="63.[151,1021,1507,1533]" box="[151,1021,1507,1533]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">
<heading id="56709A5AFFCDFFD1FF3CFA494EB962FF" bold="true" box="[151,1021,1507,1533]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" reason="1">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFCDFFD1FF3CFA494EB962FF" bold="true" box="[151,1021,1507,1533]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFCDFFD1FF3CFA494E0B62FF" authority="Melo, Walker Jr. &amp; Klepadlo" authorityName="Melo, Walker Jr. &amp; Klepadlo" box="[151,847,1507,1533]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lavenbergi">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFCDFFD1FF3CFA494C9862FF" bold="true" box="[151,476,1507,1533]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Pseudoscopelus lavenbergi</emphasis>
Melo, Walker Jr. &amp; Klepadlo
</taxonomicName>
species group
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0D382D36FFCDFFD1FF3CF98748C2614A" blockId="63.[151,1436,1581,1928]" box="[151,1414,1581,1608]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFCDFFD1FF3CF9874C7A6145" bold="true" box="[151,318,1581,1607]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Composition.</emphasis>
The 
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFCDFFD1FED1F9844FFC6145" box="[378,696,1582,1607]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lavenbergi">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFCDFFD1FED1F9844FFC6145" box="[378,696,1582,1607]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Pseudoscopelus lavenbergi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group is composed of a single species: 
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFCDFFD1FB4DF984483A6145" box="[1254,1406,1582,1607]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lavenbergi">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFCDFFD1FB4DF984483A6145" box="[1254,1406,1582,1607]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">P. lavenbergi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="459D7EBDFFCDFFD1FF6DF9FF4F64608A" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="0D382D36FFCDFFD1FF6DF9FF4F64608A" blockId="63.[151,1436,1581,1928]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFCDFFD1FF6DF9FF4C02616D" bold="true" box="[198,326,1621,1647]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The 
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFCDFFD1FE29F9FC4F84616D" box="[386,704,1622,1647]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lavenbergi">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFCDFFD1FE29F9FC4F84616D" box="[386,704,1622,1647]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Pseudoscopelus lavenbergi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group is diagnosed from its congeners by three unique characteristics of photophore pattern: 
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFCDFFD1FDF1F9D44F326195" box="[602,630,1662,1687]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">trf</emphasis>
in a broad band of three or more rows (
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFCDFFD1FBF7F9D449E46195" box="[1116,1184,1662,1687]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">vs. trf</emphasis>
absent in 
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFCDFFD1FAB6F9D448D86195" box="[1309,1436,1662,1687]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="scutatus">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFCDFFD1FAB6F9D448D86195" box="[1309,1436,1662,1687]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">P. scutatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFCDFFD1FF63F90C4CD861BD" box="[200,412,1702,1727]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="astronesthidens">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFCDFFD1FF63F90C4CD861BD" box="[200,412,1702,1727]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">P. astronesthidens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species groups; in a single row with widely spaced photophores in 
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFCDFFD1FB1FF90C480461BD" authorityName=", YPM" authorityYear="2798" box="[1204,1344,1702,1727]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="altipinnis">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFCDFFD1FB1FF90C480461BD" box="[1204,1344,1702,1727]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">P. altipinnis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group, and in a single row of closely spaced photophores, with a medial cluster in 
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFCDFFD1FBCDF96449A561E5" box="[1126,1249,1742,1767]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="scriptus">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFCDFFD1FBCDF96449A561E5" box="[1126,1249,1742,1767]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">P. scriptus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group); 
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFCDFFD1FF3CF95C4D87600D" box="[151,195,1782,1807]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">ptvf</emphasis>
short, not reaching anus, and extending anteriorly only halfway to pelvic-fin origin (
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFCDFFD1FB7BF95C4863600D" box="[1232,1319,1782,1807]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">vs. ptvf</emphasis>
elongate, extending close to anus, and extending anteriorly to very close to pelvic-fin origin in all the other species); 
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFCDFFD1FAD9F8B448D86035" box="[1394,1436,1822,1847]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">mxf</emphasis>
completely absent and 
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFCDFFD1FE0EF8EC4C8E605D" box="[421,458,1862,1887]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">apf</emphasis>
present (
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFCDFFD1FD93F8EC4F13605D" box="[568,599,1862,1887]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">vs.</emphasis>
both 
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFCDFFD1FD30F8EC4F81605D" box="[667,709,1862,1887]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">mxf</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFCDFFD1FD55F8EC4E60605D" box="[766,804,1862,1887]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">apf</emphasis>
absent on 
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFCDFFD1FC09F8EC495B605D" box="[930,1055,1862,1887]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="scutatus">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFCDFFD1FC09F8EC495B605D" box="[930,1055,1862,1887]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">P. scutatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group; both 
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFCDFFD1FAB8F8EC487C605D" box="[1299,1336,1862,1887]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">apf</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFCDFFD1FAD9F8EC48D8605D" box="[1394,1436,1862,1887]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">mxf</emphasis>
present in the remaining species).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
